Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving automatic speech recognition (ASR) systems using sequence-to-sequence models.
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with speech signals and their processing.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper proposes a new training strategy for ASR models using reinforcement learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of AI-based ASR systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with optimizing a system (ASR) using a reinforcement learning algorithm.
